What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: English 114 is phenomenal. Take it with Professor Gosselink, you will not regret it.

Great class, wonderful professor, and enthusiastic students. Even though I am an exchange student and English is my second language, the workload is not so heavy; three essays, one presentation, and ten reading articles for discussion. This class does not only focus on writing strategy, but also discussion skill and presentation. My favorite class at Yale.
A great class to strengthen your writing techniques for college. Would highly recommend taking this course.

Despite being annoying at times, I would definitely recommend this section of ENGL 114 to others. The final paper is pretty much on whatever you want it to be and instead of doing 4 papers in the term, you do 3 and a presentation, which turned out to be really nice.

I would recommend this course as a rigorous introduction to American writing, especially for foreign students. Furthermore, if you are interested in development economics or global thinking, this is the course for you.
